EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 142300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING E AND THEN NWARDS
FM ENGLAND AND WALES WILL AFFECT MUCH OF CULLERCOATS. MEANWHILE AN AREA OF
LOW PRESSURE 984 CENTRED OVER ICELAND AT APPROXIMATELY 65 N 15 W WILL AFFECT
THE FAR N W OF CULLERCOATS. THIS LOW MOVS SLWY SWARDS THROUGH THURSDAY EVENING
AND FRIDAY DISPLACING THE RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE EWARDS. AS THE LOW THEN
PUSHES EWARDS THROUGH SATURDAY AND SUNDAY IT FILLS TO APPROXIMATELY 1002
BUT MAINTAINS A CYCLONIC INFLUENCE ACROSS THE NERN HALF OF CULLERCOATS. MEANWHILE
THE SERN HALF MAINTAINS A SLACK PRESSURE PATTERN WITH A RENEWED INFLUENCE
OF RIDGING DUE TO A LARGE AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING UP FM THE AZORES.
WINDS ARE LIKELY TO BE NON-HAZARDOUS FOR MOST SEA AREAS THROUGHOUT THIS PERIOD
HOWEVER DURING FRIDAY NIGHT AND SATURDAY STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY TO AFFECT
FAIR ISLE ESPECIALLY ACROSS THE W OF THE AREA. THESE WILL MOD AGAIN THROUGH
